                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/233: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-09T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 9, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. Department’s no. 206, August 8, 7 p.m., and your no. 257, August 11, 4 p.m.
                    In as much as the Iranian Minister in Washington has received no reply from his
                    Government to his cable regarding Dr. Millspaugh, please inform the Department
                    whether objection is being raised to Dr. Millspaugh’s appointment or whether he
                    still appears to be acceptable to the Iranian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
